** ''[[Nalgaeset Hangul Input Method Editor]]'' (날개셋 한글 입력기); Kim Yongmook, South Korea){{snd}} A hangul input method which is especially made for the 3(se)-beolsik keyboard layout (only works on Microsoft Windows).
** ''Nabi'' ({{lang|ko|나비}}), ''ami'' ({{lang|ko|아미}}; South Korea){{snd}} Allows to type hangul on [[Linux]].
** ''[[m17n]]''{{snd}} Allows to use revised romanization for hangul input on Unix.
** ''[[Smart Common Input Method|SCIM]]'' and ''[[Intelligent Input Bus|iBus]]''{{snd}} Allows one to type hangul and hanja on [[POSIX]]-style operating systems including Linux and [[Berkeley Software Distribution|BSD]].
* [[Word processor]]s{{snd}} All programs listed below include domestic hangul fonts, non-hangul fonts and a hangul-[[hanja]] conversion utility.
** ''[[Hangul (word processor)|Hangul]]'' ([[Haansoft Corporation|Haansoft]], South Korea)
** ''[[Changdok|Ch'angdŏk]]'' ({{lang|ko-Hang|창덕}}; PIC,<ref name="khs"/> North Korea){{snd}} This popular program exists in an [[MS-DOS]] version developed in April 1990 [https://web.archive.org/web/20031125231703/http://preview.britannica.co.kr/spotlights/nkorea/society/b20c1792n0.html] and a Windows version developed in 1996.<ref name="howfar">{{cite web |url=http://www.tongilnews.com/article.asp?mainflag=Y&menuid=102000&articleid=2511 |script-title=ko:북한의 컴퓨터산업 어디까지 왔나 |author=[[Yonhap]] |work=Tongilnews.com |date=1998-01-07 |language=Korean |accessdate=2006-12-03}} {{Dead link|date=September 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> It includes a peculiar [[Cult of personality#Kim Il-sung and Kim Jong-il|personality cult]] feature by which pressing {{Key press|Ctrl|I}} or {{Key press|Ctrl|J}} produces titles exalting [[Kim Il-sung]] and [[Kim Jong-il]], respectively.<ref name="dgNK100">{{Cite web |url=http://www.kplibrary.com/nkterm/read.aspx?num=989 |title=북한용어사전: 평양정보센터(PIC) |language=Korean |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928060407/http://www.kplibrary.com/nkterm/read.aspx?num=989 |archive-date=2007-09-28 |access-date=2006-12-03}}</ref>

== Hangul in Unicode ==
{{see also|List of Hangul jamo}}

Hangul letters are detailed in several separate parts of the Unicode specification:
* [[Hangul Syllables]] (AC00–D7A3)
* [[Hangul Jamo (Unicode block)|Hangul Jamo]] (1100–11FF)
* [[Hangul Compatibility Jamo]] (3130–318F)
* [[Hangul Jamo Extended-A]] (A960–A97F)
* [[Hangul Jamo Extended-B]] (D7B0–D7FF)

=== Hangul Syllables block ===
The precomposed hangul syllables in the Hangul Syllables block in Unicode are algorithmically defined, using the following formula:
: [(initial) × 588 + (medial) × 28 + (final)] + 44032

